# Sample documents
documents = ["Natural language processing and machine learning are closely related.",
             "Economics and finance involve the study of wealth and money management.",
             "Machine learning involves the creation of algorithms that can learn from data."]

# Tokenization and removal of stopwords
from nltk.corpus import stopwords
nltk.download('stopwords')
stop_words = stopwords.words('english')

texts = [[word for word in document.lower().split() if word not in stop_words]
         for document in documents]

# Building a dictionary
dictionary = corpora.Dictionary(texts)

# Creating a document-term matrix
corpus = [dictionary.doc2bow(text) for text in texts]

# Applying LDA (Latent Dirichlet Allocation)
lda_model = models.LdaModel(corpus, num_topics=2, id2word=dictionary, passes=15)

# Results
topics = lda_model.print_topics(num_words=4)
for topic in topics:
    print(topic)

# Ensure nltk resources are available
nltk.download('stopwords')
nltk.download('wordnet')
nltk.download('omw-1.4')

# Function to preprocess text
def preprocess_text(text):
    # Convert text to lowercase
    text = text.lower()
    # Remove punctuation
    text = text.translate(str.maketrans('', '', string.punctuation))
    # Remove numbers and other non-letters
    text = re.sub(r'[^a-z\s]', '', text)
    # Tokenization
    tokens = word_tokenize(text)
    # Remove stopwords
    stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
    tokens = [word for word in tokens if word not in stop_words]
    # Lemmatization
    lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
    tokens = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(word) for word in tokens]
    return ' '.join(tokens)

# Apply preprocessing to the specific column
data['processed_recommendations'] = data['What recommendations would you make to sports organisations to grow baseball\'s popularity in India?'].apply(preprocess_text)

# Function to preprocess text
def preprocess_text(text):
    # Convert text to lowercase
    text = text.lower()
    # Remove punctuation
    text = text.translate(str.maketrans('', '', string.punctuation))
    # Remove numbers and other non-letters
    text = re.sub(r'[^a-z\s]', '', text)
    # Tokenization
    tokens = word_tokenize(text)
    # Remove stopwords
    stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
    tokens = [word for word in tokens if word not in stop_words]
    # Lemmatization
    lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
    tokens = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(word) for word in tokens]
    return ' '.join(tokens)

# Apply preprocessing to the specific column
data['processed_recommendations1'] = data['Please share any additional comments or suggestions regarding the promotion or development of baseball in India'].apply(preprocess_text)


from collections import Counter

# Concatenate all preprocessed text into one large string
all_text = ' '.join(data['processed_recommendations1'])

# Tokenize the concatenated string
all_tokens = word_tokenize(all_text)

# Count the frequency of each token
token_counts = Counter(all_tokens)

# Display the most common tokens
print(token_counts.most_common(10))


from textblob import TextBlob

# Function to get sentiment
def get_sentiment(text):
    blob = TextBlob(text)
    return blob.sentiment.polarity

# Apply sentiment analysis on the preprocessed text
data['sentiment'] = data['processed_recommendations1'].apply(get_sentiment)

# Overview of sentiments
print(data['sentiment'].describe())

from gensim import corpora, models

# Prepare data for LDA analysis
texts = [text.split() for text in data['processed_recommendations1']]
dictionary = corpora.Dictionary(texts)
corpus = [dictionary.doc2bow(text) for text in texts]

# Apply LDA model
lda_model = models.LdaModel(corpus, num_topics=5, id2word=dictionary, passes=15)

# Print the topics
for idx, topic in lda_model.print_topics(-1):
    print('Topic: {} \nWords: {}'.format(idx, topic))

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

file_path = r"C:\Users\ISG\Downloads\A Market Analysis to Assess the Potential for Baseball in India\A Market Analysis to Assess the Potential for Baseball in India.csv"
data = pd.read_csv(file_path)

#print(data.head())
#print(data.describe())
#print(data.info())

# Example mapping
response_mapping = {
    'Not influential at all': 1,
    'Not very influential': 2,
    'Somewhat influential': 3,
    'Extremely influential': 4
}

data['Influence_Numeric'] = data['How influential are celebrities and sports influencers in shaping your interest in sports like baseball?'].map(response_mapping)


plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.barplot(x='Influence_Numeric', y='Please select your age group', data=data, ci=None)
plt.title('Influence of Celebrities and Sports Influencers by Age Group')
plt.xlabel('Mean Influence Score')
plt.ylabel('Age Group')
plt.show()
